article.description: Tyler Reynolds registered 12 points as Manhattan edged past Quinnipiac 62-58 on Sunday.
article.headline: Reynolds scores 12 to lift Manhattan past Quinnipiac 62-58
article.linkText: Reynolds scores 12 to lift Manhattan past Quinnipiac 62-58
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. -- Tyler Reynolds registered 12 points as Manhattan edged past Quinnipiac 62-58 on Sunday. Warren Williams had 11 points for Manhattan (10-20, 8-10 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Nehemiah Mack added 10 points and seven rebounds. Tykei Greene had seven rebounds for the visiting team. Rich Kelly had 17 points for the Bobcats (16-13, 11-7). Cameron Young added 16 points and six rebounds. Abdulai Bundu had seven rebounds. The Jaspers evened the season series against the Bobcats with the win. Quinnipiac defeated Manhattan 63-59 on Jan. 3. The Jaspers and the Bobcats next take the floor in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference Tournament. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
